<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Manners (long response)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Argil, Magician at Large">Argil, Magician at Large</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:40 a.m. 23/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Manners (long response)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/veeshan.cgi?read=118" TARGET=_self>Manners</A> (deacide)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>For what it's worth, I've noted that the newbie areas are far and away the worst areas for abusive behavior and offensive language. Keep in mind that Greater Faydark is the most obvious example of these, as it is actually TWO newbie areas at once. I turned off /ooc the first day I bought the game, but I like to leave /shout and /auction on; I still have to run through Greater Fay to avoid being deafened!

<P>I've also found that as I've gained levels and explored new areas, some are worse than others. I would say that Greater Fay, Crushbone, Butcherblock, Freeport (all of it), and West Commons are the areas with the most prevalent offensive behavior. [Please don't be insulted if I just listed your home; I'm just making an observation based on my own limited experience] I know that there are many, many fine folks in these zones, but for some reason they also seem to have a higher incidence of rude players. Go figure. It is worth noting that all these areas are either newbie zones or directly adjacent to newbie zones...
<P>I've found that Lesser Fay, Northern Ro, the Cauldron, Kithicor, West Commons, and especially SteamFont and Misty Thicket *seem* to have a higher level of civilized behavior. I don't pretend to understand why. Unfortunately, most of these are only advisable for mid-level characters (at least 8th; mid-teens forWest Commons and the Cauldron unless you have a great group). However, the last two (SteamFont and Misty Thicket) have monsters to carry you from 1st through 12th levels.
<P>Hope this helps some of you avoid some unpleasantness. By using /ignore and sticking to less-popular zones, I've been mostly able to do so.
<P>Argil,
<BR>Magician at Large
<BR>Lost Order of Akalabeth
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
